      "writtenOn": "2020-04-08T19:02:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Re: Tick(): It\u0027s possible, though unlikely given all the pipelining in GPUs. I actually wanted to move the Active buffers to Busy before the onFinishFlush(), which would avoid this problem, but I needed to know which ones were Active to know which ones to re-map after (in mapStagingBuffers). I also had a \"NewlyBusy\" list before for this purpose, but it was pretty gross.\n\n(TBH I don\u0027t even remember why I added this Tick(); it\u0027s possible that it\u0027s no longer necessary. If we were really flushing we should Tick() until a fence fires anyway; one Tick doesn\u0027t guarantee anything.)\n\nAnother idea might be to provide a function to move a buffer from Active to Busy, and let the backend control it. Then at least we could do it before Tick().\n\nRe: Vulkan: I think we should probably prototype something in Vulkan with this stuff before trying to anticipate all the use cases preemptively.",
      "parentUuid": "f67e59e4_92052935",
